--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages ethtool.

This utility allows querying and changing settings such as speed, port,
autonegotiation, PCI locations and checksum offload on many network devices,
especially of ethernet devices.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: ethtool
       ethtool_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: ethtool
       ethtool_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  ethtool_state
    Specify predetermined 'ethtool_state' variable (string).
    Notice: 'ethtool' is a core package on RedHat and CentOS based systems and
    can therefore not be removed.

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DEPENDENCIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGES
  ethtool: >= 3.12
    RedHat, CentOS, Gentoo

